I double-checked this by looking at wards that were *not* rearranged in the same resolution. Since "Xã Phú Ngọc" wasn't listed, it further solidifies the merger.

To cement the conclusion, I then checked the "New Wards" data, and there it was: "Xã Định Quán" confirmed, with the code "26206," also in "Tỉnh Đồng Nai".

Therefore, "Xã Phú Ngọc" no longer exists as a separate administrative unit; it's now part of the new "Xã Định Quán". The evidence is clear, with a direct citation and confirmation in the new wards data.
